# Annual Benchmark Ladder

- Maintain an annual ratchet for both fidelity and runtime performance.
- Ratchet targets may hold or tighten; they may not relax without an ADR that defines rollback window and recovery path.
- Keep benchmark scenarios, seeds, and runner class stable for year-over-year comparability.
- Require cycle closeouts to report progress against current year ladder targets.
- If annual ratchet target is missed:
  - mark status as partial,
  - create corrective ADR,
  - carry unresolved target into next annual thesis.
- Use `docs/governance/benchmark-ladder.md` as source guidance.
